@node "intro-install" "Introduction and Installation"

pccard.library is a shared library to parse PC Card (PCMCIA) data. It is
mainly intended for use by PC Card device drivers.

To install pccard.library, run the Install script. Developer files must be
installed manually.

pccard.library needs OS 2.0 or greater.

@endnode


@node "developer" "Information for Developers"

The purpose of the library is to convert the tightly packed Card Information
Structure (CIS) tuples into more manageable tag lists. CIS tuples are read
from a card using the card.resource function CopyTuple().

The library has just two functions. PCCard_GetTupleInfo() converts a tuple
and PCCard_FreeTupleInfo() frees the resultant tag list. See the @{"autodocs" link "Developer/pccard.doc/MAIN"}
for details.

At present, only a few tuple types can be handled by the library. Please ask
if you need other types parsed for your project.

Include files for @{"C" link "Developer/Include/C/libraries/pccard.h/MAIN"} and @{"assembly language" link "Developer/Include/Assembly/libraries/pccard.i/MAIN"} are provided.

@endnode


